oneBucket2Split10Elements10Width

public void oneBucket2Split10Elements10Width()
                                      throws java.lang.Exception
Generates 10 test element with a width of 10 (keys are 1, 11, 21, 31, 41, 51, 61, 71, 81 and 91). The elements are stored with the DRUMS. The bucket is split into two halves. So there will be two buckets with the following elements:
  • First bucket: 1, 11, 21, 31, 41
  • Second bucket: 51, 61, 71, 81, 91

Throws:
java.lang.Exception
